subSubSection.paragraph:
RADULA (
Fig. 3D
). Teeth arranged in wide-angle U-shape with half row formula: 1–(15–16)–65 teeth. Central tooth symmetrical tricuspid with pointed cusps; mesocone large lanceolate, dull cusp; ectocones very small. Lateral teeth asymmetrical tricuspid; mesocone large with pointed cusp; endocone very small, located near tip; ectocone larger than endocone, located in middle of tooth. Marginal teeth starting around tooth numbers 15–16, obliquely bicuspid; endocone large, pointed cusp; ectocone small. Outermost teeth gradually reduced in size from elongate, narrow teeth to very short teeth.
